  "Approximately 30,000 square meters": "",
  "Approximately 15,000 square meters": "",
  "Approximately 37,500 square meters": "",
  "s = (200+300+250)/2 = 375. Area = sqrt(375 * 175 * 75 * 125) = sqrt(375 * 175 * 75 * 125) = sqrt(615,234,375) ≈ 24,804. Using more precise calculation: sqrt(375*175*75*125) ≈ 24,206 sq m.": "",
  "A pilot flies 200 km on a bearing of 060 degrees, then turns and flies 150 km on a bearing of 150 degrees. How far is the pilot from the starting point? The angle between the two legs is 90 degrees.": "",
  "175 km": "",
  "350 km": "",
  "250 km": "",
  "300 km": "",
  "Since the angle between the two legs is 90 degrees, this forms a right triangle. Distance = sqrt(200^2 + 150^2) = sqrt(40000 + 22500) = sqrt(62500) = 250 km.": "",
  "A ship captain needs to determine the distance between two islands. From the ship, island A is 8 km away and island B is 12 km away. The angle between the two lines of sight from the ship is 110 degrees. How far apart are the islands? Use cos(110) approximately equal to -0.342.": "",
  "Approximately 10.5 km": "",
  "Approximately 14.0 km": "",
  "Approximately 20.0 km": "",
  "Approximately 16.3 km": "",
  "Using the Law of Cosines: d^2 = 8^2 + 12^2 - 2(8)(12)cos(110) = 64 + 144 - 192(-0.342) = 208 + 65.664 = 273.664. d = sqrt(273.664) ≈ 16.54 km, approximately 16.3 km.": "",
  "An architect designs a triangular roof section with two sides of 4 meters and 6 meters meeting at a 45-degree angle. What is the area of this triangular section? Use sin(45) = sqrt(2)/2 ≈ 0.707.": "",
